are not subject to the steady-state\nacceleration along continuously open flux tubes assumed in the $f_s$-$v_{obs}$\nrelationship. In general, dynamics at the boundary between open and closed\nfield lines such as interchange reconnection will invalidate the steady-state\nassumptions of this relationship.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 31 Jul 2020 16:38:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-08-03"}
